<br>
Knowing strengths &amp; weaknesses...<br>
As my knowledge grows through research and hands-on experience I will post more information pertinent to this topic.<br>
<br>
&quot;Resistance factor&quot;<br>
I have compiled this list for us in order to understand the natural resistance factors involving ourselves and our enemies.<br>
<br>
Albions ~NET=0%<br>
Briton: None ~NET=n/a<br>
Avalonian: None ~NET=n/a<br>
Saracen: Fire +5%, Cold -5% ~NET=0%<br>
Highlander: Fire -5%, Cold +5% ~NET=0%<br>
<br>
Midgard ~NET=15%<br>
Norseman: Fire -10%, Cold +10% ~NET=0%<br>
Dwarf: Fire -5% Cold +10% Earth +5% Light -5% Void +5% Mana +5% Poison +10% ~NET=+25%<br>
Kobold: Elec -10% ~NET=-10%<br>
Troll: Slash +5% Thrust +5% Crush -5% Fire -15% Cold +10% ~NET=0%<br>
<br>
Hibernia ~NET=-15%<br>
Celt: None<br>
Elf: Poison -10% ~NET=-10%<br>
Lurikeen: Dark -10% ~NET=-10%<br>
Firblog: Fire +5% Cold +5% Elec -5% Wind +5% Earth +5% Dark -5% Body -5% ~NET=5%<br>
<br>
As you can see, we are a fairly well balanced realm without any true strengths or weaknesses, regarding our resistance factors.<br>
<br>
In order to facilitate a high level view of what I am attempting to show, let us take a look at it on a realm by realm basis.<br>
We, Albions, are the most balanced out of all the realms.<br>
We have a net resistance value of 0% as a whole.<br>
The most resistant being Midgard and the least being Hibernia.<br>
<br>
I have broken down the form of resistance into two groups.<br>
This grouping is based purely on the form of &quot;commonness&quot;, in reality there can potentially be some cross over in between these groups (ex. poisoned slashing weapons).<br>
<br>
Now, breaking it down let us analyze the resistance factors regarding melee combat vs. non-melee combat.<br>
Please note that this is from a &quot;resistance point of view&quot; only.<br>
Melee combat... (Resistance factors analyzed - Slash, Thrust &amp; Crush)<br>
Strong:<br>
Trolls are incredibly tough. They are naturally resistant to what can be easily construed as the most common form of melee combat - Slash &amp; Thrust. Couple that with armor, magical items and spell support... Ouch.<br>
No other race can make this statement in any realm.<br>
<br>
Weak<br>
No race in any realm has an advantage or disadvantage.<br>
<br>
Non-Melee Combat... (Resistance factors analyzed - Everything else!!!)<br>
Let us take a look in the realm point view (as opposed to races)<br>
Strong<br>
Midgard has a net resistance value of +15%. Ouch. That mean overall, in all forms of combat combined together, Midgard as a whole is very resistant to all forms of combat damage.<br>
Weak<br>
Hibernia as a whole has a net -15% resistance value, but at the same time Midgard has a total negative resistance value of -50%. On top of that all of them except for the Kobold are very susceptible to fire, can u say Albion Wizards?<br>
<br>
Next posting...<br>
I will attempt try to come up with best and worst match ups between class types vs. races, based on their resistance factor.<br>
<br>
Courage &amp; Glory<br>
&quot;I'm really gonna hate fighting Trolls...&quot; - Wyndsor<br>
